  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note_45",
      "text": "Computes the cross-correlogram of two series (A = the first input, B = the second): the correlation between A and B at each lag from -maxLag to +maxLag, using the overlapping segment only. The peak lag is the delay between the signals — a peak at a positive lag means B leads A by that many samples. Use it to find the phase relationship between two rhythms, or the response delay between a driver and a follower. Choose Pearson (linear) or Spearman (rank); leave max lag at 0 to auto-pick a quarter of the shorter series. Quick-plot draws the correlogram (lag vs r). Chatfield, The Analysis of Time Series.",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 24,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 190
    }
